A quote from @stephenmrcovey. One of my “mentors “ in my early adult life.  He’s the author of a book called The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People.  Covey states in habit #2 that you must Begin with the End in Mind.

There can be so many distractions, from social media, to the business of the day to day, to meeting your “goals”  And if you haven’t defined what your “Main thing” is then you could be charging 100 mph in the wrong direction 🤷🏼‍♀️ 

I find when I take time to drop in, feel into my purpose, define it, then take action toward it, that is when it all flows. 

When I’m making daily decision, even small ones, like should I go to lunch with this person, or should I make time to work out today, or should I send that email, or should I buy that new outfit, or should I go hang with my munchkins,  I do so through the lens of what my main thing is. 

Who am I? What’s my purpose? And is this thing that I’m considering going to move me closer in alignment with my dharma?

Drop and emoji of the things that distract you and keep you from keeping the main thing the main thing 😉
👧🏽👩🏼‍💻🧳🐶🍱📱💵🔮📚

.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#purpose #alignment #focus #dharma #7habits #7habitsofhighlyeffectivepeople #stephencovey #mainthing #awakening #entrepreneur

I can not stress enough how important time blocking is in my life.  I do a brain dump the night before of all of those things swirling around my head.  Then when the morning comes I spend a few minutes organizing and prioritizing based on what is in alignment with my purpose. From there I breeze through the day knowing that I’ve got it all handled 🙌🏾

Exception… sick kids, a dog that throws up on the carpet, a friend that needs some extra time from you, and or insert any number of things.  Not all is lost!! A quick recalibrations can get you back to the “main thing” quicker than you think 🧐 ❤️

Also… most days end up wearing outfits like this, cause fashion and hair brushing are low on my priorities 💃🏽
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

For so many years I thought that to live a happy life you didn’t entertain negative emotions. You kept the pain tucked away.  Hidden from all and mostly myself. I’m good, life’s good.  And it was. And something deep inside of me was yelling for attention.

I believed that my “shadow” parts were bad, ugly and no one wanted to see them especially me.  I selected partners that validated that. For love was given to me when I was good, happy, fun, or strong. Love was revoked when I was experiencing other emotions.

This slow unraveling, a revealing of my light, has brought light to the shadows. I’m no longer abandoning any of me… the really fun vibes or the really ugly ones.

When I began loving all of me a funny thing happened.  I began magnetizing people into my life that wanted to know all of me. They are honored to witness all of my soul.

And exploring even deeper into my human existence lies a knowing that I am whole, divinely designed to serve, but I am the light. Not separate, but of it. And who am I to fully accept and love the divine?

All of this has lead me to a place of allowance and spaciousness. I’m honored to be a student of the eternal 🙏🏽
.

#magicallife #nonduality #spirituality #spiritualawakening #shaddowwork #godeep #allow #spaciousness #

Let’s talk. 
Something that has always been very present in my world has been my commitment to honoring my passions. These are the things that I’m uniquely designed to do/be. The entrepreneurial spirit in me has moved me to create an energy exchange for my gifts. 
Our society is set up to do this with money. So when I can offer my gifts to the would it’s a natural place to create a “business” of this. 
When I’m feeling fear around releasing something new to the world, I’m reminded that this is not about me. I am a channel of wisdom based on the lessons presented throughout my life. My role is to share that, and in return be gifted an exchange.
So, my friends… when you’re looking to put some new art into the world, whether that be your jewelry, your organizing skills, your photography, your coaching, whatever your amazing gift to offer is, reminder to get out of the way. This isn’t all about you. This is about the sharing of wisdom, art, and beauty.
.

Edit: And IG is glitching out today so you’ll have to use context clues at the end or just listen to my voice 😜
.
.

My heart and soul are so heavy. 💔 Seven years ago today I had to tell my babies their Dad died, he had crossed over and wouldn’t be coming back. The following years I was so angry with him. How could you leave me to raise the kids alone? How could you leave the kids without a dad? How was I going to do this? Why us?

Hey, last year I went on a quest to heal. To heal the pieces of me that I had left shattered. For how are my kids to heal if I haven’t? So inward I went….

I went back, back into the darkness. I explored all of my parts. Everything that felt destroyed, wronged, and enraged.
What I found when I went looking, was forgiveness, understanding, compassion, strength, resilience, and love… Unconditional love. 

None of it made sense at the time, and through the process of healing I was shown why this is our path. 

And now… the support and clarity I feel as a single mom is powerful. I am not alone in the journey and this is path I’m intended to walk. With love and leadership, I am guiding the way.

To all of the people in the Middle East experiencing some of the worst atrocities I’ve ever witnessed….my heart, my soul, my everything is with you. May the light shine on the understanding,… In time. 💔.
.
.
.
.
.
#release #compassion #understanding #death #lossofafather #grief #healing #forgiveness
